properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 14 at 2:58PM PST until January 15 at 4:00PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Small Craft Advisory, southeast winds 20 to 30
kt. For the Gale Watch, southeast winds 30 to 40 kt possible.

* WHERE...Admiralty Inlet.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, from midnight tonight to
4 PM PST Wednesday. For the Gale Watch, from Wednesday
afternoon through Thursday morning.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
A Gale Watch is issued when the risk of gale force winds of 34 to
47 knots has significantly increased, but the specific timing
and/or location is still uncertain. It is intended to provide
additional lead time for mariners who may wish to consider
altering their plans.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO 4 PM PST WEDNESDAY... ...GALE WATCH IN EFFECT FROM WEDNESDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH THURSDAY MORNING
